{
    "poem_title": "ÉPÎTRE XV",
    "author": "",
    "structure": "suite périodique",
    "year": "1706-1778",
    "manually_checked": false,
    "stanzas": [
        {
            "stanza_number": 1,
            "stanza_type": null,
            "lines": [
                {
                    "line_number": 1,
                    "line_text": "Je voulais par quelque huitain,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "0"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 2,
                    "line_text": "Sonnet, ou lettre familière,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "1"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 3,
                    "line_text": "Réveiller l'enjouement badin",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "0"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 4,
                    "line_text": "De votre altesse chansonnière ;",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "1"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 5,
                    "line_text": "Mais ce n'est pas petite affaire",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "1"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 6,
                    "line_text": "À qui n'a plus l'abbé Courtin",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "0"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 7,
                    "line_text": "Pour directeur et pour confrère.",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "1"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 8,
                    "line_text": "Tout simplement donc je vous dis",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "2"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 9,
                    "line_text": "Que dans ces jours, de Dieu bénis,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "2"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 10,
                    "line_text": "Où tout moine et tout cagot mange",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "3"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 11,
                    "line_text": "Harengs saurets et salsifis,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "2"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 12,
                    "line_text": "Ma muse, qui toujours se range",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "3"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 13,
                    "line_text": "Dans les bons et sages partis,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "2"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 14,
                    "line_text": "Fait avec faisans et perdrix",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "4"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 15,
                    "line_text": "Son carême au château saint-Ange.",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "3"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 16,
                    "line_text": "Au reste, ce château divin,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "0"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 17,
                    "line_text": "Ce n'est pas celui du saint-père,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "1"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 18,
                    "line_text": "Mais bien celui de Caumartin,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "0"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 19,
                    "line_text": "Homme sage, esprit juste et fin,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "0"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 20,
                    "line_text": "Que de tout mon cœur je préfère",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "1"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 21,
                    "line_text": "Au plus grand pontife romain,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "0"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 22,
                    "line_text": "Malgré son pouvoir souverain",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "0"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 23,
                    "line_text": "Et son indulgence plénière.",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "1"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 24,
                    "line_text": "Caumartin porte en son cerveau",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "5"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 25,
                    "line_text": "De son temps l'histoire vivante ;",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "6"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 26,
                    "line_text": "Caumartin est toujours nouveau",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "5"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 27,
                    "line_text": "À mon oreille qu'il enchante ;",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "6"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 28,
                    "line_text": "Car dans sa tête sont écrits",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "7"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 29,
                    "line_text": "Et tous les faits et tous les dits",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "7"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 30,
                    "line_text": "Des grands hommes, des beaux esprits ;",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "7"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 31,
                    "line_text": "Mille charmantes bagatelles,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "8"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 32,
                    "line_text": "Des chansons vieilles et nouvelles,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "8"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 33,
                    "line_text": "Et les annales immortelles",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "8"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 34,
                    "line_text": "Des ridicules de Paris.",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "2"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 35,
                    "line_text": "Château saint-Ange, aimable asile,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "9"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 36,
                    "line_text": "Heureux qui dans ton sein tranquille",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "10"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 37,
                    "line_text": "D'un carême passe le cours !",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "11"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 38,
                    "line_text": "Château que jadis les amours",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "11"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 39,
                    "line_text": "Bâtirent d'une main habile",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "9"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 40,
                    "line_text": "Pour un prince qui fut toujours",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "11"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 41,
                    "line_text": "À leur voix un peu trop docile,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "9"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 42,
                    "line_text": "Et dont ils filèrent les jours !",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "11"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 43,
                    "line_text": "Des courtisans fuyant la presse,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "12"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 44,
                    "line_text": "C'est chez toi que François Premier",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "13"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 45,
                    "line_text": "Entendait quelquefois la messe,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "12"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 46,
                    "line_text": "Et quelquefois par le grenier",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "13"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 47,
                    "line_text": "Rendait visite à sa maîtresse.",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "12"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 48,
                    "line_text": "De ce pays les citadins",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "14"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 49,
                    "line_text": "Disent tous que dans les jardins",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "14"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 50,
                    "line_text": "On voit encor son ombre fière",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "1"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 51,
                    "line_text": "Deviser sous des marronniers",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "15"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 52,
                    "line_text": "Avec Diane De Poitiers,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "15"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 53,
                    "line_text": "Ou bien la belle Ferronière.",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "1"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 54,
                    "line_text": "Moi chétif, cette nuit dernière,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "1"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 55,
                    "line_text": "Je l'ai vu couvert de lauriers ;",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "15"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 56,
                    "line_text": "Car les héros les plus insignes",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "16"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 57,
                    "line_text": "Se laissent voir très-volontiers",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "15"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 58,
                    "line_text": "À nous, faiseurs de vers indignes.",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "16"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 59,
                    "line_text": "Il ne traînait point après lui",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "17"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 60,
                    "line_text": "L'or et l'argent de cent provinces,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "18"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 61,
                    "line_text": "Superbe et tyrannique appui",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "17"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 62,
                    "line_text": "De la vanité des grands princes ;",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "18"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 63,
                    "line_text": "Point de ces escadrons nombreux",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "19"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 64,
                    "line_text": "De tambours et de hallebardes,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "20"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 65,
                    "line_text": "Point de capitaine des gardes,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "20"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 66,
                    "line_text": "Ni de courtisans ennuyeux ;",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "19"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 67,
                    "line_text": "Quelques lauriers sur sa personne,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "21"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 68,
                    "line_text": "Deux brins de myrte dans ses mains,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "14"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 69,
                    "line_text": "Étaient ses atours les plus vains ;",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "14"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 70,
                    "line_text": "Et de v…vérole quelques grains",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "14"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 71,
                    "line_text": "Composaient toute sa couronne.",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "21"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 72,
                    "line_text": "« Je sais que vous avez l'honneur,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "22"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 73,
                    "line_text": "Me dit-il, d'être des orgies",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "23"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 74,
                    "line_text": "De certain aimable prieur,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "22"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 75,
                    "line_text": "Dont les chansons sont si jolies",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "23"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 76,
                    "line_text": "Que Marot les retient par cœur,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "22"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 77,
                    "line_text": "Et que l'on m'en fait des copies.",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "23"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 78,
                    "line_text": "Je suis bien aise, en vérité,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "13"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 79,
                    "line_text": "De cette honorable accointance ;",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "24"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 80,
                    "line_text": "Car avec lui, sans vanité,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "13"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 81,
                    "line_text": "J'ai quelque peu de ressemblance :",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "24"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 82,
                    "line_text": "Ainsi que moi, Minerve et Mars",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "25"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 83,
                    "line_text": "L'ont cultivé dès son enfance ;",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "24"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 84,
                    "line_text": "Il aime comme moi les arts,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "26"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 85,
                    "line_text": "Et les beaux vers par préférence ;",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "24"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 86,
                    "line_text": "Il sait de la dévote engeance,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "24"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 87,
                    "line_text": "Comme moi, faire peu de cas ;",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "27"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 88,
                    "line_text": "Hors en amour, en tous les cas",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "27"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 89,
                    "line_text": "Il tient, comme moi, sa parole ;",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "28"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 90,
                    "line_text": "Mais enfin, ce qu'il ne sait pas,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "27"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 91,
                    "line_text": "Il a, comme moi, la v…vérole ;",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "28"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 92,
                    "line_text": "J'étais encor dans mon été",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "13"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 93,
                    "line_text": "Quand cette noire déité,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "13"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 94,
                    "line_text": "De l'amour fille dangereuse,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "29"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 95,
                    "line_text": "Me fit du fleuve de Léthé",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "13"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 96,
                    "line_text": "Passer la rive malheureuse.",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "29"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 97,
                    "line_text": "Plaise aux dieux que votre héros",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "30"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 98,
                    "line_text": "Pousse plus loin ses destinées,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "31"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 99,
                    "line_text": "Et qu'après quelque trente années",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "31"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 100,
                    "line_text": "Il vienne goûter le repos",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "30"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 101,
                    "line_text": "Parmi nos ombres fortunées !",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "31"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 102,
                    "line_text": "En attendant, si de Caron",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "32"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 103,
                    "line_text": "Il ne veut remplir la voiture,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "33"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 104,
                    "line_text": "Et s'il veut enfin tout de bon",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "32"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 105,
                    "line_text": "Terminer la grande aventure,",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "33"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 106,
                    "line_text": "Dites-lui de troquer Chambon",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "32"
                },
                {
                    "line_number": 107,
                    "line_text": "Contre quelque once de mercure. »",
                    "metrical_pattern": null,
                    "line_length": "8",
                    "rhyme": "33"
                }
            ],
            "stanza_text": "Je voulais par quelque huitain,\nSonnet, ou lettre familière,\nRéveiller l'enjouement badin\nDe votre altesse chansonnière ;\nMais ce n'est pas petite affaire\nÀ qui n'a plus l'abbé Courtin\nPour directeur et pour confrère.\nTout simplement donc je vous dis\nQue dans ces jours, de Dieu bénis,\nOù tout moine et tout cagot mange\nHarengs saurets et salsifis,\nMa muse, qui toujours se range\nDans les bons et sages partis,\nFait avec faisans et perdrix\nSon carême au château saint-Ange.\nAu reste, ce château divin,\nCe n'est pas celui du saint-père,\nMais bien celui de Caumartin,\nHomme sage, esprit juste et fin,\nQue de tout mon cœur je préfère\nAu plus grand pontife romain,\nMalgré son pouvoir souverain\nEt son indulgence plénière.\nCaumartin porte en son cerveau\nDe son temps l'histoire vivante ;\nCaumartin est toujours nouveau\nÀ mon oreille qu'il enchante ;\nCar dans sa tête sont écrits\nEt tous les faits et tous les dits\nDes grands hommes, des beaux esprits ;\nMille charmantes bagatelles,\nDes chansons vieilles et nouvelles,\nEt les annales immortelles\nDes ridicules de Paris.\nChâteau saint-Ange, aimable asile,\nHeureux qui dans ton sein tranquille\nD'un carême passe le cours !\nChâteau que jadis les amours\nBâtirent d'une main habile\nPour un prince qui fut toujours\nÀ leur voix un peu trop docile,\nEt dont ils filèrent les jours !\nDes courtisans fuyant la presse,\nC'est chez toi que François Premier\nEntendait quelquefois la messe,\nEt quelquefois par le grenier\nRendait visite à sa maîtresse.\nDe ce pays les citadins\nDisent tous que dans les jardins\nOn voit encor son ombre fière\nDeviser sous des marronniers\nAvec Diane De Poitiers,\nOu bien la belle Ferronière.\nMoi chétif, cette nuit dernière,\nJe l'ai vu couvert de lauriers ;\nCar les héros les plus insignes\nSe laissent voir très-volontiers\nÀ nous, faiseurs de vers indignes.\nIl ne traînait point après lui\nL'or et l'argent de cent provinces,\nSuperbe et tyrannique appui\nDe la vanité des grands princes ;\nPoint de ces escadrons nombreux\nDe tambours et de hallebardes,\nPoint de capitaine des gardes,\nNi de courtisans ennuyeux ;\nQuelques lauriers sur sa personne,\nDeux brins de myrte dans ses mains,\nÉtaient ses atours les plus vains ;\nEt de v…vérole quelques grains\nComposaient toute sa couronne.\n« Je sais que vous avez l'honneur,\nMe dit-il, d'être des orgies\nDe certain aimable prieur,\nDont les chansons sont si jolies\nQue Marot les retient par cœur,\nEt que l'on m'en fait des copies.\nJe suis bien aise, en vérité,\nDe cette honorable accointance ;\nCar avec lui, sans vanité,\nJ'ai quelque peu de ressemblance :\nAinsi que moi, Minerve et Mars\nL'ont cultivé dès son enfance ;\nIl aime comme moi les arts,\nEt les beaux vers par préférence ;\nIl sait de la dévote engeance,\nComme moi, faire peu de cas ;\nHors en amour, en tous les cas\nIl tient, comme moi, sa parole ;\nMais enfin, ce qu'il ne sait pas,\nIl a, comme moi, la v…vérole ;\nJ'étais encor dans mon été\nQuand cette noire déité,\nDe l'amour fille dangereuse,\nMe fit du fleuve de Léthé\nPasser la rive malheureuse.\nPlaise aux dieux que votre héros\nPousse plus loin ses destinées,\nEt qu'après quelque trente années\nIl vienne goûter le repos\nParmi nos ombres fortunées !\nEn attendant, si de Caron\nIl ne veut remplir la voiture,\nEt s'il veut enfin tout de bon\nTerminer la grande aventure,\nDites-lui de troquer Chambon\nContre quelque once de mercure. »"
